Tuberculosis (TB) is a communicable disease that affects mainly lungs but can affect any organ in the body. Common symptoms of TB include: Fever, night sweats, weight loss or unintended weight gain, cough, blood in sputum, chest pain, shortness of breath and abdominal pain (1-2).

