Tuberculosis is caused by Mycobacterium tuberculosis complex.

Response:
The symptoms of tuberculosis are usually mild and nonspecific. These include fever, night sweats, weight loss, fatigue, anorexia, abdominal pain (with peritoneal TB), chest pains (with pleural effusion) or a persistent cough with blood in the sputum (suggestive of pulmonary Tb).

